The PPF's Mzwanele Manyi is responding to reports in Sunday newspapers that he tried to get positions at state-owned entities JOHANNESBURG - President of the Progressive Professional s Forum Mzwanele Manyi says he's sees nothing wrong with helping people get jobs.Manyi, who is a former government spokesperson, has responded to weekend reports that he approached the Gupta family seeking positions at a state-owned-entities for himself and attorney Xoliswa Mpongoshe.The Sunday Times and City Press also revealed how the Guptas were in direct communication with government ministers.Manyi says he's done nothing wrong. Did I get a CV from Xoliswa? Without a doubt, yes I did. Did I try assist her to into various boards and so on? Yes, I did do that, and I do that for many other people. (Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)